  "body": "Kubelet issues a docker inspect call after creating a container, but for very short lived containers there is a window in which they could exit before being inspected [1]. Specifically, I'm referring to [this line](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/35c9ca853a084a4ea04debe027c6ea680fd9ddac/pkg/kubelet/dockertools/manager.go#L1493) in the docker manager.\n\nIf the container PID is 0, we should check the ExitCode and other relevant fields and handle them appropriately.\n\n[1] This is the suspected cause of several flakes:\nhttp://kubekins.dls.corp.google.com/job/kubernetes-e2e-gke/7253/\nhttp://kubekins.dls.corp.google.com/job/kubernetes-e2e-gce-container-vm/25/\nhttp://kubekins.dls.corp.google.com/job/kubernetes-e2e-gce-container-vm/32/\n\n/cc @kubernetes/sig-node @bprashanth @smarterclayton @zmerlynn \n",
